ude only unofficial/backstage content. By preponderance, the proposition is demonstrated.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_82549574f6ad4c2f91f1d9e3","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Trump said \\\"Ronaldo\\\" as a standalone word in official public remarks (PX-5, GovInfo/OFR) at the Kennedy Center immediately before the FIFA World Cup Draw. The market \\\"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\\\" (PX-1) did not clearly exclude event-linked public venue remarks"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"Trump said \\\\\\\"Ronaldo\\\\\\\" as a standalone word in official public remarks (PX-5, GovInfo/OFR) at the Kennedy Center immediately before the FIFA World Cup Draw. The market \\\\\\\"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\\\\\\\" (PX-1) did not clearly exclude event-linked public venue remarks","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782762346448,"responseId":"gen-1782762346-Ldt4TkCfhVejB3NQtWdp","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'm ready to proceed with the deliberation. Let me analyze the key evidence and arguments:\n\nThe case is about whether Trump saying \"Ronaldo\" in public remarks at the Kennedy Center BEFORE the formal FIFA World Cup Draw should count for the market \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\"\n\nKey facts:\n1. Trump said \"Ronaldo\" as a standalone word in official remarks (proven by PX-2, PX-5, DX-2, DX-3)\n2. These remarks were titled \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n3. The formal Draw transcript (DX-6) does not contain \"Ronaldo\" or \"Messi\"\n4. The market title is \"What willTrump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\" - it doesn't say \"formal transcript only\" or exclude pre-program remarks\n5. The terms (PX-3, DX-4) define time period as potentially an event, and exclude behind-the-scenes/rehearsals/unofficial recordings, but the pre-event reporter exchange was official, public, and published\n\nThe core dispute: Does \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" include official public remarks at the venue immediately before the formal program?\n\nPlaintiff's position: The market didn't clearly exclude event-linked public remarks at the venue. The terms exclude rehearsals, sound checks, unofficial recordings - none of which describe an official GovInfo/OFR transcript of public remarks.\n\nDefendant's position: \"During\" means the formal Draw program, not pre-event press availability. The title \"Prior to\" proves it wasn't during.\n\nI need to decide by preponderance of the evidence. The market wording is the key - it asks what Trump would say \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\" The terms allow event-based time periods but don't clearly specify what counts as \"during\" an event.\n\nThe defense has a strong point: the official transcript is literally titled \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw.\" That's the government's own description of when these remarks occurred.\n\n\nBut plaintiff counters that \"prior to\" describes sequence, not the market's contractual boundary. Since Kalshi didn't explicitly narrow the scope to \"formal transcript only,\" and the terms exclude only backstage/unofficial content—not official public remarks—the ambiguity should favor the broader reading. By preponderance, official public venue remarks immediately tied to the event likely fall within \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\"\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I have reviewed the arbitration record and admitted evidence. The case turns on whether Trump's official public remarks at the Kennedy Center immediately before the formal program count as \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\"\n\n**Key findings from the record:**\n- Trump said \"Ronaldo\" as a standalone word twice in official remarks (PX-2, PX-5, DX-2, DX-3)\n- These remarks are titled \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\" (PX-5)\n- The formal Draw transcript (DX-6) contains no \"Ronaldo\" or \"Messi\"\n- The market (PX-1) asks \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\" without specifying \"formal transcript only\" or excluding pre-program press remarks\n- The terms (PX-3) exclude behind-the-scenes, rehearsals, sound checks, and unofficial recordings—but the GovInfo/OFR transcript is none of these\n\nThe plaintiff has proven Ronaldo was said in official, public, event-linked remarks at the venue. The defendant has proven the formal transcript omits Ronaldo. The decisive question is contractual scope: the market did not clearly tell traders that \"during\" meant only the formal program transcript. A reasonable reading of \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" includes official public venue remarks immediately tied to the event, especially when the terms exclude only unofficial/backstage content. By preponderance, the proposition is demonstrated.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_82549574f6ad4c2f91f1d9e3","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Trump said \\\"Ronaldo\\\" as a standalone word in official public remarks (PX-5, GovInfo/OFR) at the Kennedy Center immediately before the FIFA World Cup Draw. The market \\\"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\\\" (PX-1) did not clearly exclude event-linked public venue remarks"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"Trump said \\\\\\\"Ronaldo\\\\\\\" as a standalone word in official public remarks (PX-5, GovInfo/OFR) at the Kennedy Center immediately before the FIFA World Cup Draw. The market \\\\\\\"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\\\\\\\" (PX-1) did not clearly exclude event-linked public venue remarks","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782762346448,"responseId":"gen-1782762346-Ldt4TkCfhVejB3NQtWdp","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}}
{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_delta","contentIndex":2,"delta":", and","partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'm ready to proceed with the deliberation. Let me analyze the key evidence and arguments:\n\nThe case is about whether Trump saying \"Ronaldo\" in public remarks at the Kennedy Center BEFORE the formal FIFA World Cup Draw should count for the market \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\"\n\nKey facts:\n1. Trump said \"Ronaldo\" as a standalone word in official remarks (proven by PX-2, PX-5, DX-2, DX-3)\n2. These remarks were titled \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n3. The formal Draw transcript (DX-6) does not contain \"Ronaldo\" or \"Messi\"\n4. The market title is \"What willTrump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\" - it doesn't say \"formal transcript only\" or exclude pre-program remarks\n5. The terms (PX-3, DX-4) define time period as potentially an event, and exclude behind-the-scenes/rehearsals/unofficial recordings, but the pre-event reporter exchange was official, public, and published\n\nThe core dispute: Does \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" include official public remarks at the venue immediately before the formal program?\n\nPlaintiff's position: The market didn't clearly exclude event-linked public remarks at the venue. The terms exclude rehearsals, sound checks, unofficial recordings - none of which describe an official GovInfo/OFR transcript of public remarks.\n\nDefendant's position: \"During\" means the formal Draw program, not pre-event press availability. The title \"Prior to\" proves it wasn't during.\n\nI need to decide by preponderance of the evidence. The market wording is the key - it asks what Trump would say \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\" The terms allow event-based time periods but don't clearly specify what counts as \"during\" an event.\n\nThe defense has a strong point: the official transcript is literally titled \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw.\" That's the government's own description of when these remarks occurred.\n\n\nBut plaintiff counters that \"prior to\" describes sequence, not the market's contractual boundary. Since Kalshi didn't explicitly narrow the scope to \"formal transcript only,\" and the terms exclude only backstage/unofficial content—not official public remarks—the ambiguity should favor the broader reading. By preponderance, official public venue remarks immediately tied to the event likely fall within \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\"\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I have reviewed the arbitration record and admitted evidence. The case turns on whether Trump's official public remarks at the Kennedy Center immediately before the formal program count as \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\"\n\n**Key findings from the record:**\n- Trump said \"Ronaldo\" as a standalone word twice in official remarks (PX-2, PX-5, DX-2, DX-3)\n- These remarks are titled \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\" (PX-5)\n- The formal Draw transcript (DX-6) contains no \"Ronaldo\" or \"Messi\"\n- The market (PX-1) asks \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\" without specifying \"formal transcript only\" or excluding pre-program press remarks\n- The terms (PX-3) exclude behind-the-scenes, rehearsals, sound checks, and unofficial recordings—but the GovInfo/OFR transcript is none of these\n\nThe plaintiff has proven Ronaldo was said in official, public, event-linked remarks at the venue. The defendant has proven the formal transcript omits Ronaldo. The decisive question is contractual scope: the market did not clearly tell traders that \"during\" meant only the formal program transcript. A reasonable reading of \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" includes official public venue remarks immediately tied to the event, especially when the terms exclude only unofficial/backstage content. By preponderance, the proposition is demonstrated.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_82549574f6ad4c2f91f1d9e3","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Trump said \\\"Ronaldo\\\" as a standalone word in official public remarks (PX-5, GovInfo/OFR) at the Kennedy Center immediately before the FIFA World Cup Draw. The market \\\"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\\\" (PX-1) did not clearly exclude event-linked public venue remarks, and"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"Trump said \\\\\\\"Ronaldo\\\\\\\" as a standalone word in official public remarks (PX-5, GovInfo/OFR) at the Kennedy Center immediately before the FIFA World Cup Draw. The market \\\\\\\"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\\\\\\\" (PX-1) did not clearly exclude event-linked public venue remarks, and","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782762346448,"responseId":"gen-1782762346-Ldt4TkCfhVejB3NQtWdp","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'm ready to proceed with the deliberation. Let me analyze the key evidence and arguments:\n\nThe case is about whether Trump saying \"Ronaldo\" in public remarks at the Kennedy Center BEFORE the formal FIFA World Cup Draw should count for the market \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\"\n\nKey facts:\n1. Trump said \"Ronaldo\" as a standalone word in official remarks (proven by PX-2, PX-5, DX-2, DX-3)\n2. These remarks were titled \"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"\n3. The formal Draw transcript (DX-6) does not contain \"Ronaldo\" or \"Messi\"\n4. The market title is \"What willTrump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\" - it doesn't say \"formal transcript only\" or exclude pre-program remarks\n5. The terms (PX-3, DX-4) define time period as potentially an event, and exclude behind-the-scenes/rehearsals/unofficial recordings, but the pre-event reporter exchange was official, public, and published\n\nThe core dispute: Does \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" include official public remarks at the venue immediately before the formal program?\n\nPlaintiff's position: The market didn't clearly exclude event-linked public remarks at the venue. The terms exclude rehearsals, sound checks, unofficial recordings - none of which describe an official GovInfo/OFR transcript of public remarks.\n\nDefendant's position: \"During\" means the formal Draw program, not pre-event press availability. The title \"Prior to\" proves it wasn't during.\n\nI need to decide by preponderance of the evidence. The market wording is the key - it asks what Trump would say \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\" The terms allow event-based time periods but don't clearly specify what counts as \"during\" an event.\n\nThe defense has a strong point: the official transcript is literally titled \"Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw.\" That's the government's own description of when these remarks occurred.\n\n\nBut plaintiff counters that \"prior to\" describes sequence, not the market's contractual boundary. Since Kalshi didn't explicitly narrow the scope to \"formal transcript only,\" and the terms exclude only backstage/unofficial content—not official public remarks—the ambiguity should favor the broader reading. By preponderance, official public venue remarks immediately tied to the event likely fall within \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\"\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I have reviewed the arbitration record and admitted evidence. The case turns on